        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 3 at 4:54PM EDT until July 3 at 6:00PM EDT by NWS Burlington VT</headline>
        <description>SVRBTV

The National Weather Service in Burlington has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Rutland County in southern Vermont...

* Until 600 PM EDT.

* At 454 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over South
Poultney, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vehicles is possible. Expect wind
damage to trees and powerlines.

* Locations impacted include...
Poultney Village, Tinmouth, Shrewsbury, Middletown Springs,
Wallingford, Lake St. Catherine, Rutland - Southern Vermont
Airport, Poultney, Clarendon, Ira, Wells, Mount Holly, Pawlet,
Mendon, East Clarendon, Chippenhook, East Wells, Cuttingsville,
Lake St. Catherine State Park, and South Poultney.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
